<concept id="concept_7FE638734ED64807B2A89B4F64AA5D04">
  <title>How Analytics Measures Unique Visitors</title>
  <shortdesc>
    Analytics measures visitors to a website by
	 using various technologies, including persistent cookies, IP addresses, user
	 agent string, or a combination of these technologies. Visitors may be reported
	 across various time periods, site sections, and pages. This white paper defines
	 the technologies used, the reporting periods, and the implications of each for
	 website managers and advertisers. 
  </shortdesc>
