    <section id="section_D70DE18C8E9743ED90F3E50D33884423">
      <title>Persistent Cookies</title>
      <p>The 
		  <uicontrol>Persistent Cookies Filter</uicontrol> in a 
		  <wintitle>Unique Visitors Reports</wintitle> (Hourly, Daily, Weekly,
		  and so on), shows the percentage of all cookie-based visitors. Analytics
		  registers the remainder of visitors (non-cookie based users) by using the
		  unique occurrence of the IP address and user agent string (the browser version,
		  captured via the HTTP header). 
		</p>
      <p>The number of persistent cookie-based users reported by 
		  Analytics is accurate (greater than 99.5%). The
		  number of non-persistent cookie-based users is less accurate because a single
		  visitor can have several IP addresses during a single visit. Or, several
		  visitors might share an IP address from behind a corporate firewall. 
		</p>
